<output>
<analysis>
<has-cmf>False. There is no CMF number present in the provided post information.</has-cmf>
<refers-to-candidate>False. The post does not refer to any parliamentary candidate by name, surname, or any other clear identifier.  It promotes an event, the Impact Festival.</refers-to-candidate>
<addresses-the-wide-population>True. The post is a paid advertisement on Facebook, a public platform, and its content is designed to reach a broad audience, not just specific individuals. The target audience is defined by age and location in the `aaa_info` section.</addresses-the-wide-population>
<electoral-objective>False. The objective of the post is to promote attendance at the Impact Festival, an event focused on sustainability and innovation. There is no discernible intention to influence voting patterns in the parliamentary elections.</electoral-objective>
<journalism>True. The post could be considered a form of public announcement or event promotion, similar to a news item about an upcoming event. It provides information about the event's schedule and themes, not advocating for a specific candidate or party.</journalism>
<personal_opinion>Not applicable. The post doesn't express personal opinions related to the elections.</personal_opinion>
</analysis>

<conclusion>
<post_id>555805780416651</post_id>
<electoral-propaganda-analysis>
The Facebook post promotes the Impact Festival, an event unrelated to the parliamentary elections.  While the post is categorized as "POLITICAL" due to its presence on Facebook's ad library, the content itself does not meet the criteria for electoral propaganda as defined by Article 36 (7) of LEGE nr. 334 din 17 iulie 2006 and Article 98 t) of LEGE nr. 208 din 20 iulie 2015. It lacks direct reference to any candidate or party, its objective is not to influence voting, and it does not fall outside the bounds of standard event promotion.  The fact that it's a paid advertisement doesn't automatically qualify it as electoral propaganda; the content itself must meet the legal definition.
</electoral-propaganda-analysis>
<electoral-propaganda-decision>FALSE</electoral-propaganda-decision>
<electoral-propaganda-candidates/>
<responsible-party-or-group>Impact Hub Bucharest</responsible-party-or-group>
<message-for-police/>
</conclusion>
</output>
